quran[202]{c,v,t}:
  23,1,The believers have succeeded
  23,2,those who are humble in their prayers
  23,3,and those who stay away from the useless (acts and talks)
  23,4,and those who do their mandatory charity
  23,5,and those who guard their private parts
  23,6,"except with their spouses or what they own, then indeed they are blameless"
  23,7,"and anyone who look for beyond this, then they are those who exceed the limits"
  23,8,and those who observe their trusts and their promise
  23,9,and those who guard their mandatory prayer
  23,10,they are the inheritors
  23,11,"those who inherit the paradise, remaining in there forever"
  23,12,And We have certainly created the human being from clay’s extract
  23,13,Then We placed him as a fertilized egg in a safe quarter (the womb)
  23,14,"Then We made the fertilized egg into a (dangling, clinging, and leach like) blood clot, then We made the clot into a (piece of) chewed flesh, then We made the chewed flesh into bones, then We covered the bones with flesh, then We turned it into another creation. So blessed is God, best of the creators"
  23,15,Then you certainly die after that
  23,16,Then indeed you are raised on the resurrection day
  23,17,"And We have certainly created seven paths/layers (of skies) above you, and We are not neglectful of the creation"
  23,18,"And We sent down rain from the sky in proper amount, then We made it settle in the earth, and indeed We are able to take it away"
  23,19,"And We produced gardens of date palms and grapes for you with it, and there are plenty of fruits in them that you eat from it"
  23,20,And a tree (of olive) that comes out of Mount Sinai producing oil and sauce/dip for those who eat
  23,21,"And there is a lesson for you in the livestock, We give you drink from what is in their bellies, and there are many other benefits for you in them, and you also eat from them"
  23,22,And you are carried on them and on the ships
  23,23,"And We have certainly sent Noah to his people, and he said: my people, serve God, you have no god other than Him, would you not be cautious"
  23,24,"The leaders of those who disbelieved among his people said: he is only a human being like you who wants to be superior over you, and if God wanted He would have sent down angels, we did not hear of this among our forefathers"
  23,25,"He is only a man that there is madness in him, so put up with him for a while"
  23,26,"He said: my Master, help me because they denied me"
  23,27,"So We revealed to him that build the Ark under Our eyes and Our revelation, and when Our command comes and the oven bursts out (with water), then put two of every kind (a male and a female) and your family in it except anyone among them whom the word is already issued against him, and do not talk to me about those who did wrong for they will be drowned"
  23,28,"And when you and those with you settle on the Ark, then say: all praise belongs to God, the One who saved us from the wrongdoing people"
  23,29,"And say: my Master, make me land in a blessed landing place, you are the best of those who make (people) land"
  23,30,"Indeed there are signs in that, and indeed We put (people) to test"
  23,31,Then We gave rise to another generation after them
  23,32,"And We sent them a messenger from among themselves (saying): serve God, you have no god other than Him, would you not be cautious"
  23,33,"And the leaders of his people, those who disbelieved and denied the meeting of the hereafter and We made them comfortable in this world’s life said: this is only a human being like you, he eats from what you eat from it and he drinks from what you drink"
  23,34,"and if you obey a human being like yourselves, then you are certainly losers"
  23,35,"Does he promise you that when you die and you become dust and bones, that you are brought out (and resurrected)"
  23,36,"What you are promised is far, far (from the truth)"
  23,37,"There is nothing except our life of this world, we die and we live (and world goes on), and we will not be raised"
  23,38,"He is only a man that makes up a lie (and attributes it) to God, and we do not believe him"
  23,39,"He said: my Master, help me because they denied me"
  23,40,"He (God) said: they shall become sorry in a short while"
  23,41,"Then the awesome roar rightfully took them, and We made them into debris. So away with the wrongdoing people"
  23,42,Then We gave rise to other generations after them
  23,43,No community (of faith) gets ahead of its appointed time and they would not delay
  23,44,"Then We sent Our messengers one after the other, every time a messenger came to a community, they denied him. So We made them follow each other (to destruction), and We made them stories (for the others). So away with people who do not believe"
  23,45,Then We sent Moses and his brother Aaron with Our signs and a clear reason
  23,46,"to Pharaoh and his assembly, but they acted arrogantly and they were bossy people"
  23,47,"They said: should we believe in two human beings like us while their people are our servants"
  23,48,So they denied them both then they became among the destroyed ones
  23,49,"And We have certainly given Moses the book, so that they may be guided"
  23,50,"And We made son of Mary and his mother a sign, and we sheltered them both on a hilltop having an accommodation and a spring (of running water)"
  23,51,"Messengers, eat from the good things and do good work, indeed I know well what you do"
  23,52,"And indeed this is your community, a single community, and I am your Master so be cautious of Me"
  23,53,"But they cut up their affair (in the religion) into pieces among them, each party happy with what they had"
  23,54,So leave them in their ignorance for a while
  23,55,Do they think that what We supplied them with it from wealth and children
  23,56,"We are rushing the goodness for them? No, they do not realize"
  23,57,Indeed those who are fearful of the awe of their Master
  23,58,and those who believe in their Master’s signs
  23,59,and those who do not associate (partners) with their Master
  23,60,"and those who give from what they are given, and their hearts trembles that they return to their Master"
  23,61,they rush in (doing) the good and they are pioneers for it
  23,62,"We do not task any person beyond its capability, and there is a book with Us that speaks the truth, and they will not be wronged"
  23,63,"No, but their hearts are in ignorance regarding this (truth), and they have works other than that, which they are doers of them"
  23,64,"Until when We take their rich ones with the punishment, then they cry out for help"
  23,65,"Do not cry out for help today, indeed you will not be helped by Us"
  23,66,"My signs had been read to you, but you used to turn back on your heels"
  23,67,"Being arrogant about them, talking nonsense (about My signs) in nightly conversation"
  23,68,"Did they not think about the word (of Quran), or did something come to them that did not come to their forefathers"
  23,69,"Or did they not recognize their messenger, so they rejected him"
  23,70,"Or do they say there is madness in him? No, but he brought them the truth, and most of them dislike the truth"
  23,71,"And if the truth had followed their desires, then the skies and the earth and everyone in them would have certainly corrupted/perished. No, but We brought them their mention/reminder, but they turn away from their mention/reminder"
  23,72,"Or do you ask them for any payment? Payment from your Master is better, and He is best of the providers"
  23,73,And you certainly invite them to a straight path
  23,74,And indeed those who do not believe in the hereafter are deviators from the (right) path
  23,75,"And if We have mercy on them and remove what is with them from harm, they would persist in their rebellion, blindly wandering"
  23,76,"And We have certainly taken them to the punishment, but they did not comply with their Master and they do not humbly plead"
  23,77,"Until when We opened a door having a severe punishment for them, then they became hopeless in it"
  23,78,And He is the One who made the ear and the eyes and the hearts for you. You give little thanks
  23,79,"And He is the One who multiplied (and spread) you on the earth, and you will be gathered to Him"
  23,80,"And He is the One who gives life and causes death, and the alternation of the night and the day belongs to Him. Do you not understand"
  23,81,"No, but they say same as what the earlier ones said"
  23,82,"They said: would we be raised when we die and become dust and bones"
  23,83,We and our fathers have certainly been promised this in the past. This is only stories of the earlier ones
  23,84,"Say: to whom belongs the earth and everyone in it, if you knew"
  23,85,"They are going to say: God. Say: do you not take notice"
  23,86,"Say: who is the Master of the seven skies and the Master of the great throne"
  23,87,"They are going to say: God. Say: would you not be cautious"
  23,88,"Say: in whose hand is the rule of everything and he shelters and no one is sheltered against him, if you knew"
  23,89,"They are going to say: God. Say: so, how are you bewitched"
  23,90,"No, but We brought them the truth, and they are certainly liars"
  23,91,"God did not take a child and there is no god with Him, in that case every god would take away what it created, and some of them would be superior to others. God is flawless about what they describe"
  23,92,"Knower of the unseen and the visible, and He is above what they associate (with Him)"
  23,93,"Say: my Master, I wish You would show me what they are promised"
  23,94,"My Master, do not make me of the wrongdoing people"
  23,95,And We are certainly able to show you what We promised them
  23,96,Repel (and respond to) the badness with that which is better. We know better about what they describe
  23,97,"And say: my Master, I look for Your protection from seductions of the devils"
  23,98,"and my Master, I look for your protection from their presence"
  23,99,"Until when the death comes to one of them, then he says: my Master, send me back"
  23,100,"so that I do good work in what I left behind (and neglected). No way, indeed it is only a word that he says it. And there is a barrier behind them until a day they are raised"
  23,101,"So when the trumpet is blown, then there is no relationship between them on that day, and they do not ask each other"
  23,102,"So those who scales are heavy, then they are the successful ones"
  23,103,"And those whose scales are light, then they are those who lost their souls, remaining in hell forever"
  23,104,"The fire burns their faces, and they frown in it"
  23,105,"Were not My signs being read to you, and you were denying it"
  23,106,"They say: our Master, our misery overcame us and we were misguided people"
  23,107,"Our Master, bring us out of it, and if we return (to disbelief) then indeed we are wrongdoers"
  23,108,"He (God) says: go away, into it and do not talk to Me"
  23,109,"Indeed there was a group of My servants saying: our Master, we believed, so forgive us and have mercy on us, and You are the best of the merciful ones"
  23,110,But you took them as a joke (and ridiculed them) and you were laughing at them until they made you forget remembering Me
  23,111,"Indeed I reward them today because of their perseverance (and patience), indeed they are the victors"
  23,112,"He (God) says: how many years did you stay in the earth (in the grave)"
  23,113,"They say: we stayed for a day or part of a day, so ask those who count"
  23,114,"He says: you only stayed a little while, if only you knew"
  23,115,"Did you think that We created you uselessly (without a purpose), and you are not returned to Us"
  23,116,"God is highest (and above all), the true king, there is no God except Him, the Master of the honorable throne"
  23,117,"And whoever calls on another god with God without having any proof for that, then indeed his accounting is with his Master. Indeed the disbelievers do not succeed"
  23,118,"And say: my Master, forgive and have mercy, and you are the best of the merciful ones"
  24,1,"(This is) a chapter which We sent it down and We made it mandatory and We sent down clear verses in it, so that you may take notice"
  24,2,"Flog each one of the adulterer/fornicator man and the adulterer/fornicator woman one hundred lashes, and do not let pity for them takes you away from God’s law if you believe in God and the last day, and a group of the believers should witness their punishment"
  24,3,"The adulterer/fornicator man should only marry an adulterer/fornicator or a polytheist woman, and the adulterer/fornicator woman should only get married to an adulterer/fornicator or a polytheist man, and that is forbidden to the believers"
  24,4,"And those who accuse chaste women, then do not bring four witnesses, then flog them eighty lashes and do not ever accept their testimony, and they are the disobedient ones"
  24,5,"Except those who repent and straighten out after that, then indeed God is forgiving and merciful"
  24,6,"And those who accuse their spouses, and there is no witnesses for them except themselves, then their individual testimony (is acceptable) if they testify four times (swearing) by God that he is certainly of the truthful ones"
  24,7,And the fifth (oath) that God’s curse be on him if he is of the liars
  24,8,And it prevents the punishment from her if she testifies four times (swearing) by God that indeed he is of the liars
  24,9,And the fifth (oath) that God’s anger be on her if he is of the truthful ones
  24,10,And if it was not for God’s grace and mercy on you (you would be in trouble). God is acceptor of repentance and wise
  24,11,"Those who brought the lie (and accusation) were a bunch of you. Do not think that it is bad for you, but it is good for you. For every one of them earned a share of the sin, and the one among them who had greatest (share) of it, has a great punishment"
  24,12,"Why when you heard it, the believing men and the believing women did not think well of themselves and they did not say: this is an obvious lie"
  24,13,"Why did they not bring four witnesses for it? So when they did not bring the witnesses, then they are the liars in God’s view"
  24,14,"And if it was not for God’s grace and mercy on you in this world and in the hereafter, a great punishment would have touched you because of what you engaged in it"
  24,15,"When you receive it through each other’s tongues and you say with your mouths what you have no knowledge of it, and you think it is insignificant, while it is significant in God's view"
  24,16,"And whey when you heard it, you did not say: it is not for us to speak of this, You are flawless, this is a great slander"
  24,17,God advises you that do not ever repeat anything like it if you are believers
  24,18,"And God clarifies the signs for you, and God is knowledgeable and wise"
  24,19,"Indeed those who like to spread the indecency among those who believed have a painful punishment in this world and the hereafter, and God knows and you do not know"
  24,20,"And if it was not for God’s grace and mercy on you, (you would be in trouble) and indeed God is gentle and merciful"
  24,21,"You who believe, do not follow Satan's footsteps, and whoever follows Satan's footsteps (should know that), indeed he instructs to the indecency and to the wrong (unacceptable). And if it was not for God’s grace and mercy on you, none of you would ever be purified (absolved), but God purifies anyone He wants. God hears all and knows all"
  24,22,"And those who have grace and plenty (of wealth) should not swear that they would not give to the relatives (and close ones), and the needy, and the migrants in God’s way, and they should excuse and overlook. Do you not like God to forgive you? God is forgiving and merciful"
  24,23,Those who accuse the unaware chaste believing women are cursed in this world and the hereafter and they have a great punishment
  24,24,on a day that their tongues and their hands and their feet testify against them for what they used to do
  24,25,"on that day God pays them back in full their rightful dues, and they know that God is the obvious truth"
  24,26,"The bad women are for the bad men, and the bad men are for the bad women, and the good women are for good men, and the good men are for good women. They are clear of what they say (about them), forgiveness and honorable provision is for them"
  24,27,"You who believe, do not enter any houses except your houses until you ask for familiarity (and permission) and greet its resident. That is better for you, so that you may take notice"
  24,28,"And if you do not find anyone in it, then do not enter it until permission is given to you, and if you are told to go back, then (do not enter and) go back, as that is purer (and better) for you. And God knows well what you do"
  24,29,There is no blame on you if you enter vacant houses in which you have goods. God knows what you disclose and what you hide
  24,30,Tell the believing men to lower their looks (and do not look lustfully) and guard their private parts. That is purer (and better) for them. God is well aware of what they do
  24,31,"And tell the believing women to lower their looks (and do not look lustfully) and guard their private parts, and they should not show their beauty except what is apparent of it, and they should put their scarves over their breasts, and they should not show their beauty except to their husbands or their fathers or their father in law or their sons or their husbands' sons or their brothers or their brothers' sons or their sisters' sons or their women (companions) or those whom their right hands own or the male dependents with no desire (of women) or children who do not know about the private parts of women, and they should not stomp their feet to expose what they hide from their beauty. And all you believers repent to God, so that you may be successful"
  24,32,"And marry off the singles among you and the righteous among your male and female servants. If they are poor, God enriches them from His grace, and God is bountiful and knowledgeable"
  24,33,"And those who do not find (any way) to marry, should abstain (from sex) until God enriches them from His bounty. And those among what your right hands own who ask for the certificate (of freedom), then write it for them if you know any good in them, and give them some of God’s possession that He gave you. And do not force your maids into prostitution looking for gain of this world’s life, if they want to be chaste. And if anyone forces them, then after their compulsion God is forgiving and merciful (to them)"
  24,34,"And We have certainly sent down to you clear (and clarifying) signs, and example of those who passed away before you, and an advice for those who control themselves"
  24,35,"God is light of the skies and the earth. Example of His light is like a lamp holder with a lamp in it, and the lamp is in a glass, the glass is as if it is a brilliant star lit by (the oil of) a blessed olive tree, that is not facing east or west, and its oil almost glows (by itself) even though fire did not touch it. Light upon light, God guides whom He wants to His light. And God gives the examples for the people, and God knows everything"
  24,36,"(This light is) in houses that God permitted His name to be raised and to be mentioned in it, and He is glorified in it in the mornings and the afternoons"
  24,37,"Men who are not distracted by business and sale (and buy) from remembering God and performing mandatory prayer and giving to mandatory charity, and they are afraid of a day that the hearts and the eyes turn around in it"
  24,38,"so that God rewards them better than what they did, and increase them (their reward) from His grace. And God provides for anyone He wants without any limit"
  24,39,"Those who disbelieved, their works are like a mirage in a desert that a thirsty person imagines it as water until when he gets to it and finds it to be nothing, and he finds God with him, and He pays his account back in full, and God is quick in accounting"
  24,40,"Or like darkness in a deep sea that a wave, over it a wave which above it is clouds, covers it. Darkness, one on top of the other (such that) when he brings out his hand, he almost does not see it, and anyone who God did not put a light for him, then there is no light for him"
  24,41,"Did you not see that everyone in the skies and the earth and the birds with their wings outspread glorify God, each one does know its prayer and its glorification. God knows well what they do"
  24,42,"And rule of the skies and the earth belongs to God, and the final return is to God"
  24,43,"Did you not see that God drives the clouds gently, then joins them together then makes it dense, then you see the raindrops comes out from within it, and He sends down hail from the sky from the mountains (of clouds) that are in it, then He strikes anyone He wants with it, and turns it away from anyone He wants, and the flash of its lightning almost takes away the sights (and blinds people)"
  24,44,God alternates the night and the day. Indeed there is a lesson in that for those who have insight
  24,45,"And God created all creatures from water, and some of them walk on their bellies and some of them walk on two legs and some of them walk on four. God creates what He wants. Indeed God is capable of everything"
  24,46,"We have certainly sent down clarifying verses, and God guides anyone He wants to a straight path"
  24,47,"And they say: we believed in God and the messenger and we obeyed. Then some of them turn away after that, and they are not the believers"
  24,48,"And when they are invited to God and His messenger to judge between them, suddenly some of them turn away"
  24,49,"And if the truth is for them (and they are right), they come to him obediently"
  24,50,"Is there a disease in their hearts, or do they doubt, or are they afraid that God and His messenger deal unfairly against them? No, but they are the wrongdoers"
  24,51,"Indeed word of the believers, when they are invited to God and His messenger to judge between them, is to say: we heard and we obeyed. And they are the successful ones"
  24,52,"And whoever obeys God and His messenger and fears God and is cautious of Him, then they are the victors"
  24,53,"They solemnly swear by God that if you order them they shall go out (to fight), say: do not swear, reasonable obedience (is enough), indeed God is well aware of what you do"
  24,54,"Say: obey God and obey the messenger, but if you turn away, he is only responsible for what he is charged with and you are responsible for what you are charged with, and if you obey him you are guided. And the messenger's responsibility is only the clear preaching"
  24,55,"God promised those who believed among you and did good works, that He shall make them successors (of power) on the earth as He made those before them successors, and He shall strengthen their religion (and way of life) for them, the one that He approved for them, and afterward He shall replace their fear with security to serve Me and not associate anything with Me, and whoever disbelieves after that, then they are the disobedient ones"
  24,56,And perform the mandatory prayer and give to the mandatory charity and obey the messenger so that you may receive mercy
  24,57,Do not think that those who disbelieved weaken/escape (God) on the earth. Their housing is the fire and it is certainly a bad destination
  24,58,"You who believe, those whom your right hands own and those (children) among you who have not reached puberty should ask your permission at three times (before coming to your room). Before morning mandatory prayer, and when you put off your clothes during noon time, and after evening mandatory prayer. (These are) three times of privacy for you. There is no blame on you or on them to circulate around you and each other at other times. That is how God clarifies the signs for you, and God is knowledgeable and wise"
  24,59,"And when the children among you reach the puberty, then they should ask permission (at all times) as those before them asked for permission. That is how God clarifies His signs for you, and God is knowledgeable and wise"
  24,60,"And the women past menopause who do not expect a marriage, then there is no blame on them if they put off their clothes without displaying their beauty. And if they avoid that, it is better for them. God hears all and knows all"
  24,61,"There is no blame on the blind and no blame on the lame (crippled) and no blame on the sick and not on yourselves if you eat in your houses or your fathers’ houses or your mothers’ houses or your brothers’ houses or your sisters’ houses or your fathers’ brothers’ houses or your fathers’ sisters’ houses or your mothers’ brothers’ houses or your mother's sisters’ houses or the houses that you have their keys or your friend’s houses. There is no blame on you if you eat together or separately. So when you enter any houses then greet each other, a blessed and pure greeting from God. That is how God clarifies the signs for you that you may understand"
  24,62,"The believers are only those who believed in God and His messenger, and when they are with him on a public matter, they do not go away until they ask his permission. Indeed those who ask your permission are those who believe in God and His messenger. So when they ask your permission for (taking care of) some of their affairs, then give permission to anyone you want among them and ask God for their forgiveness. Indeed God is forgiving and merciful"
  24,63,Do not make the messenger’s call between you the same as a call from each other. God does know those among you who slip away hiding away (behind others). So those who oppose His/his order should beware of a disaster happening to them or a painful punishment happening to them
  24,64,"Know that indeed everything in the skies and the earth belongs to God, He does know what you are up to it (and your intentions), and He tells them of what they did on a day that they are returned to Him. And God knows everything"
  25,1,"Blessed is the One who sent down the criterion to His servant, to be a warning for humankind"
  25,2,the One that rule of the skies and the earth belongs to Him and He did not take a child and there is no partner for Him in the rule and He created everything and determined it proportionately
  25,3,"And they took gods other than Him that do not create anything and they are created, and they have no power to harm or benefit themselves, and they have no power over death and life and resurrection"
  25,4,"And those who disbelieved said: this (Quran) is only a lie that he made up and other people have helped him with it. So they have certainly committed wrongdoing and lie"
  25,5,"And they said: (these are) stories of the earlier ones that he copied it and it is dictated to him morning and afternoon"
  25,6,"Say: the One who knows the secret of the skies and the earth sent it down. Indeed He is forgiving and merciful"
  25,7,"And they said: what is with this messenger that he eats the food and he walks in the markets (and streets), why was not an angel sent down to him to be a warner with him"
  25,8,"Or a treasure is not given to him, or there is no garden for him to eat from it? And the wrongdoers said: you are only following a bewitched man"
  25,9,"See how they gave examples about you, they are lost and they cannot find a way"
  25,10,"Blessed is the One who gives you better than that if He wants, gardens which rivers flow through them and He gives you palaces"
  25,11,"No, but they denied the hour and We prepared a burning fire for anyone who denies the hour"
  25,12,"When it sees them from a far place, they hear it raging and roaring"
  25,13,"And when they are thrown into a tight place of it, chained together, there they call for death"
  25,14,"Today do not call for death once, but call for death many times"
  25,15,"Say: is this better or the eternal garden that was promised to those who control themselves? It (garden) is a reward and a destination for them"
  25,16,"They have whatever they want in there, remaining forever. This is a promise that is your Master’s responsibility"
  25,17,"And a day He gathers them and whatever they served other than God, then He says: did you misguide these My servants or did they lose the way"
  25,18,"They say: You are flawless, it is not appropriate for us to take any protector other than You, but You gave them and their fathers joy (and comfort) until they forgot the reminder and they became doomed people"
  25,19,"So they have denied you in what you say, therefore you cannot turn away (the punishment) or get any help (yourselves). And whoever does wrong among you, We make him taste a great punishment"
  25,20,"And We did not send any of the messengers before you unless they ate food and walked in the market, and We made some of you a test for the others, would you persevere? And your Master sees all"